Lecture-2:

Scheduling in Different Systems:

Batch System:
No real time user. Shob kaj parallelly howa joruri na.
throughput, turnaround time, cpu utilization maximize/minimie korte chay.
throughput - kaj done per unit time (maximize korar cheshta kora hoy)
turn around time - submitted time theke finishing time er difference (minimize 
korar cheshta kora hoy), see example of fcfs.

Interactive systems:
onek user thakte pare. response time is important. response time is: output na
dekhate parleo user ke response deya j kaj shuru hoise. Preemption needed, as 
parallelism dorkar hote pare, ja preemption enable kora chara impossible.
arekta kaj: proportionality ensure kora, mane kajer size onujai kaj korar time
fix hobe. ei sense ta holo proportionality. jemon logout korte kom time lagbe.

Real time system:
deadline meet kora uddessho. ekta time thake (delta t), sheta holo deadline.
process kora data ei delta t time er moddhe shesh korte hobe.
predictable hoite hobe. ar behaviour non uniform na. eije delta t time por por 
output dekhano hocche, output predictable hobe.
example: game khela, guli korar shathe shathei ber hote hobe.

shob system er target:
- fairness ensure kora
- policy enforce kora (kono ekta certain kaj age hoite hobe, then onno gula.
jemon biis er registration. mane, ekta kaj age hoite hobe, then baki shob 
parallely cholte parbe, eije ekta kaj age korte hobe, ei decission neya holo 
policy making)

Batch System Algorithms:
- non-preemptive (eta majhe moddhe crucial, karon majhe moddhe oneeeek kaj korte
hoy, ejonno preemptive kore shudhu shudhu kaj switching e time waste korar mane
hoy na, time period onek lomba hole)
- preemptive algorithms with long period is acceptable

FCFS(First Come First Serve):
queue te rakhbo, arki. Very simple.




